reviews.text:
招呼差不在話，杯、碟又油，炒饭又咸，油菜一啖入口就成口泥，粉果酸左仲唔想取消張單，又多蚊滋，行去廁所，一打開通道門已经聞到味，行到入去就恶臭添，驚嚇道極高，奇怪係点可以过到食环果關呢？
今时今日仲点可以生存到呢？
一位前輩經理好有性格，唔理你。一位女部長好好。好多蚊知仔飛來飛去。
熱到抽筋。好似冇冷氣噉。
價錢平，食物質素麻麻!
經常晨運經過都在金港買早餐回家吃，這裡外賣七時巳營業，還有不錯的燒臘外賣，真方便

result.adr_address: Hong Kong, Wan Chai, 港灣道香港會議展覽中心金紫荊廣場
result.formatted_address: Hong Kong, Wan Chai, 港灣道香港會議展覽中心金紫荊廣場
result.name: Golden Bauhinia Restaurant

reviews.text:
Food of noisy uneducated China tourists.
Waiters are impolite and racist. They treat China tourists much better than all others.

Disappointing dim sum restaurant. Soft shell crab was very fresh but the batter was overwhelming and somewhat greasy without adding flavor. The steamed dumplings were too dense and the skins too thick, flavors did not come through at all. Excellent service though.  Total price was $30 which is too high though everything at the convention center is more expensive.  Definitely would not go out of my way to eat here, much better options elsewhere.
The environment is good. Food & service is satisfactory with very reasonable price. The service of valet parking is excellent.

It is located near the exit to the Golden Bauhinia Plaza.  Quite a long walk from the main entrance of the Hong Kong Convention and Exhibition Center with mediocre signs along the way.
The place is small but spacious, well decorated and clean.

We went for the relatively pricey $248 Dim Sum all-you-can-eat.  The selection is not as big as some of the other dim sum restaurants' offerings, but the quality is good in general.  While two of our orders went missing, it was relatively easy to track them down since the orders were put into a computer.  Also there was no time limit, you could sit there for the whole 12-2:30pm lunch slot if you like.  The waiters are well trained and speak English reasonably well.  One should note that some of the choices on the menu/ordering sheet are for each piece,  while others are for per person which usually have bigger portions.

Recomended dishes: Soup of the day (vegetables and pork broth on the day we visited), Deep Fried Shrimp Toast topped with Sesame,  Beef Shank with Spicy Sauce (a cold dish), Fried Rice with Diced Barbecue Pork and Vegetables, Poached Beancurd Sheet Rolls in Tomato Soup.

Dishes to Avoid: Fried Noodles with Shredded Pork in Premium Soy Sauce (a bit  greasy), Beef Short Ribs with Garlic (too much fat on most of the ribs)

Before I retire, I used this restaurant to entertain my visiting VIPs and performed inside the exclusive dining rooms. I have done it again on December 6, 2018 to entertain the World Intellectual Property Organisation delegation. The food, the service and the environment were superb!
